SIMPLE: emulsify
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emulsify
<hw>E*mul"si*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Emuls</ets>ion + <ets>-fy</ets>.]</ety> <def>To convert into
an emulsion; to form an emulsion; to reduce from an oily substance to a
milky fluid in which the fat globules are in a very finely divided
state, giving it the semblance of solution; <as>as, the pancreatic juice
<ex>emulsifies</ex> the oily part of food</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emulsin</ent>⟦br⟧
